She has been accused of stealing the Northcliff ANCYL branch. Thuthukile Zuma, the daughter of President Zuma and Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, allegedly rented bouncers to stop some ANC Youth League members from participating in a meeting.The meeting was to elect new leaders for the league&rsquo;s Bheki Mkhize branch in Northcliff, Johannesburg.An insider who did not want to be named claimed that she stole the branch "Thuthu has been trying to get her hands on that branch and she finally did it," It is claimed that she was voted secretary of the branch at a five-star hotel in Randpark Ridge after chaos broke out at the Windsor Recreation Centre.Zuma was previously the branch&rsquo;s chair, the position of secretary however is believed to hold more power.She is the youngest of Jacob Zuma&rsquo;s daughters with Dlamini-Zuma. When approached for comment, she referred News24 to league regional convenor Mangaliso Khonza.Khonza denied that Zuma was at fault.However, several sources told News24 that she was to blame for the row during the branch's election. One source, who did not want to be named, said this was Zuma&rsquo;s second attempt to become branch secretary."We know she is being positioned in order to facilitate a pronouncement for her mom as the next ANC president from both the region and the province," said an ANCYL member who was at the centre.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/zumas-daughter-accused-of-stealing-ancyl-branch-20170524